The paper discusses the training and prediction schedules of a character-level recurrent neural network, which is a common topic in machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the effectiveness of the model, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
